ques
for any node , if the diff in left and right subtree is > 1 then its not balanced  

approach 

*************** brute force *******************

1 on every node calculate its left and right subtree height 
2 find diff , if diff > 1 return -1;
3 this process is done on every node 

tc - n2 / sc h balanced

tc - n2 / sc n skewed


****************** optimal ************************

1 use post order dfs to calculate its height
2 while returning from the tree from leaf node as its the natural odering of dfs calc height diff also 
3 if height diff is > 1 return <bool,int> = {false,diff}
4 once you got false return false while skipping other function calls 

tc - n , sc - h balanced

tc - n / sc n skewed
